Commands needed to run simulation.R

Running 3 conversations per condition with profiles C2 and C4
Rscript simulation.R n=1 recipe=pesto_alla_genovese user="llama3:70b" agent="deepseek-r1:8b" profiles="C1,C2,C3,C4,C5" energy=0 outdir="outputs/pesto_test"

Rscript simulation.R n=3 recipe="pesto_alla_genovese" user="llama3:70b" agent="deepseek-r1:8b" profiles="C2,C4" energy=0 outdir="test_runs"


Running from a schedule.
bash mk_schedule.sh 30000
bash my_driver.sh run_schedule.tsv --user "llama3:70b" --agent "deepseek-r1:8b" --energy 1 --outdir "outputs/large_run"

Running with nohup

To keep it running after you log out, wrap the second command with nohup and &:

nohup nohup bash my_driver.sh > "sim_run_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S)_$$.log" 2>&1 & disown



nohup detaches the process from the terminal.

> large_run.log 2>&1 sends all output (stdout + stderr) to a log file.

& backgrounds the job.

You can then:

check progress in real time:

tail -f large_run.log


see if the job is still running:

ps aux | grep my_driver.sh


or list all background jobs started with nohup:

jobs -l